  "intro": "Decir in the preterite is common with indirect object pronouns because we often tell something to someone. Use me, te, le, nos, and les before dije, dijiste, dijo, dijimos, and dijeron.",
  "overview": {
    "body": "The structure is simple: indirect object pronoun + decir in the preterite + what was said. Le dije la verdad means I told him or her the truth.",
